Grand Poobah is a term that originates from [[Gilbert and Sullivan]]'s [[The Mikado]].  In this [[operetta]], the character Poo-Bah holds the exalted offices of Lord Chief Justice, Master of the Buckhounds, Groom of the Back Stairs, and Lord High Everything Else.  The name has come to be used as a mocking title for someone important or high-ranking and who exhibits an inflated self-regard.

== Pop Culture References ==

[[Fred Flintstone]] and his friend [[Barney Rubble]] were members of the Loyal Order of Water Buffaloes Lodge No. 26.  A high ranking elected position within this organization is Grand Poobah or Grand Imperial Poobah.

